Oh and one more thing:

You don't HAVE to watch a show you don't enjoy for content. YOU can tell your viewers that you don't want to watch it because you don't have a desire to.

SO hey, write your essays, make your critique videos about the show, do whatever it is that you do to help you remember the joy YOU had over the series. 

Just take a step back and say to yourself: 

"....you know what? I'mma watch something else."

This is when you take a look back and you cherish what you had and be glad that that someone younger than you now has a show they can watch and have the same feeligns of joy you had when you watched it.

You're going to experience this a lot sadly, there are going to be a lot of things you enjoyed in the past that now you don't feel connected to and that is perfectly fine, it's called growing up. THat doesn't mean you should stop enjoying that thing though.

Also, yes I get it, it is good to be critical of a show. However if you are feeling a disconnect from a series, that's a strong sign that you aren't the target audience anymore. 

And guess what, that isn't a bad thing at all.
